---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import XfiLogo from "../../components/XfiLogo.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | XiaomiHub XFI">
  <section class="container-shell py-12 sm:py-14 lg:py-16">
    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[0.72fr_0.28fr] lg:items-start">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-xiaomi">About</p>
        <h1 class="mt-4 text-[clamp(2.25rem,7vw,3.25rem)] font-bold leading-tight text-zinc-950">Community facilitation for Xiaomi development</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="panel rounded-xl p-5">
        <XfiLogo variant="main" class="h-auto w-full max-w-[280px] lg:ml-auto" />
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-base leading-7 text-zinc-600">
      XiaomiHub | XFI helps facilitate transparent community crowdfunding to support Xiaomi device development and maintainer ecosystems.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base leading-7 text-zinc-600">
      All crowdfunding contributions are fully returned to the maintainers or development teams responsible for managing the related device source and community projects.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="panel rounded-xl p-5">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Facilitation</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-600">
          XFI helps organize, bridge, and document collaboration between maintainers, device communities, and supporters.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="panel rounded-xl p-5">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Full Allocation</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-600">
          XFI is not profit-oriented. Campaign results are allocated to the related maintainer, developer, team, or development purpose.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="panel rounded-xl p-5">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Transparency</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-600">
          Goals, totals, updates, and closure status stay public so community supporters can verify the campaign story over time.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
